C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\all\API007Data\API007NVData.c
      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      API007NVData module implementation
      5           *
      6           *  @details	This module is responsible for managing the NVData(Non-Volatile) by the all types of expansion and HMI boards
      7           *
      8           *
      9           *
     10           *
     11           *		Definitions 			Details
     12           *
     13           *		NVData				- 	Non Volatile Data, Data which can be retrieved even after power failure event
     14           *								Project team shall be very cautions defining which data supposed to be NVData and not
     15           *
     16           *		Server 				- 	Management of the Data storing and restoring in the Non Volatile Data Memory
     17           *      						Performing the NVData Write/Read requests from the client
     18           *      						Here ACU shall be the Server (As in Nucleus only ACU knows how to store and retrieve the NVData)
     19           *
     20           *      Client 				- 	Management of requesting the NVData from the Server or Sending the NVData to the server to store
     21           *
     22           *      Client ID			- 	Node ID itself is used as Client ID at the server side
     23           *
     24           *      _appliance_segment	-	This is the tag/segment name used to segregate the data in appliance segment
     25           *      						A data which holds the appliance information qualifies this tag
     26           *      						For example - Max Cool, Max ICE remaining time, Cooking Selection, Dryer option selection
     27           *
     28           *      						Example -
     29           *      						#pragma location = "_appliance_segment"
     30           *      						static uint8 User_MaxCool_Option;
     31           *
     32           *
     33           *      _statistics_segment	-	This is the tag/segment name used to segregate the data in statistics segment
     34           *      						A data which holds the statistics information qualifies this tag
     35           *      						For example - Number of Normal Washing Cycles run, Number of Days Refrigerator running
     36           *
     37           *      						Example -
     38           *      						#pragma location = "_statistics_segment"
     39           *      						static uint16 Washing_Cycle_Count;
     40           *
     41           *		_header_segment		-	Only used by the module to store the overall memory crc (this segment shall not be used by the user)
     42           *
     43           *		Client Block Data	- 	Client NVData memory is divided into blocks
     44           *								These each block has its own block crc
     45           *								data is continuously monitored to see the changes
     46           *								Only that block is sent whose block crc changes, this way we can optimize sending data to the server
     47           *
     48           *		Client Block Crc	- 	Crc locally used for each block to detect easily which block changed its data
     49           *
     50           *		CDT					- 	Client Description Table used by the server
     51           *								Refer 'CLIENT_DESCRIPT_TYPE' for details
     52           *
     53           *
     54           *
     55           *
     56           *
     57           *		Client Responsibility
     58           *		1. Client role only applies to non ACU boards only
     59           *		2. Client software shall only use the '_appliance_segment and '_statistics_segment' tag to define the NVData
     60           *		3. Node Id itself treated as client ID in this module
     61           *		4. Before proceeding Read/Write operations, its responsibility of Client to claim the NVData size from Server during boot-up
     62           *		5. If the Client fails to claim the NVData then it shall remain in the error state
     63           *		6. Client shall read the previously stored NVdata from server and compare with 'previously stored crc' If it matches then data is restored or else data is corrupted
     64           *		7. If the Server is non-responsive during boot-up after the API007NVDATA_CLIENT_MSG_RETRY_COUNT number of retries shall enter to the error state
     65           *		7. Its responsible for managing NVdata of more then one blocks, it should have a track of blocks index's
     66           *		8. Its responsible to write blocks only who's block's crc is changed
     67           *		9. Shall use Arbitrary method of finding which block data is changed so that every block gets equal chance.
     68           *		10.Block shall be sent to the client with minimum time delay to avoid communication overflow (API007NVDATA_CLIENT_DATA_UPDATE_RATE_MS)
     69           *		11. During boot up it takes time to read and verify the NVData from Server Client Application shall consider this timing
     70           *          Recommended to wait until the status becomes other then API007NVDATA_RESTORE_IN_PROGRESS
     71           *
     72           *
     73           *
     74           *
     75           *
     76           *		Server Responsibility
     77           *		1. ACU is always be the Server
     78           *		2. Server features shall be enabled even if one client is present in the network
     79           *		3. Server shall support more then one client and distinguish them by node id as their client id (API007NVDATA_SERVER_NUM_CLIENTS_SUPPORT)
     80           *		4. Enough memory shall be reserved for Server so that it can serve those claims from client
     81           *		5. Server not responsible for managing the Crc of the clients
     82           *		6. If the previously stored claim does not match with the new Claim then server shall allocate new claim if its able to allocate or else reject the request
     83           *		7. If the claim is failed then server shall notify to the client
     84           *		8. If any Read/Write request are made then Server shall satisfy those requests only and shall not be involved in managing the data index etc
     85           *
     86           *
     87           *
     88           *
     89          	@startuml(Module_Diagram.png)
     90          
     91          		object API007NVData
     92          		object API007BulkData
     93          		object API007App
     94          
     95          		API007Data_NVData <|-- API007NVData
     96          
     97          		API007Data_App <|-- API007BulkData
     98          		API007BulkData <|-- API007App
     99          
    100          	@enduml
